CompanyName.label: Company Name
CompanyName.value: National Rural Utilities Cooperative Finance Corporation

CompanyDescription.label: Company Description
CompanyDescription.value: The National Rural Utilities Cooperative Finance Corporation (CFC) is a member-owned nonprofit cooperative that provides financial products to America's rural electric cooperative network. CFC was established in 1969 to raise funds from the capital markets to supplement the loan programs for electric cooperatives offered by the U.S. Department of Agriculture's (USDA) Rural Utilities Service (RUS), previously Rural Electrification Administration (REA).
